Introduction This resource is an observation of a Mammography Fibroadenoma. It is typically one observation of a set of related observations that comprise a finding. This and its related obsevations are all referenced by a parent 'section' observation by that parents 'Observation.hasMember' element.
Graphical Overview
This graph provides an overview of how and where Mammography Fibroadenoma is referenced,and what items Mammography Fibroadenoma itself references.
Review Status
NotReviewed
Member Fields
The following are parts of this observation that are contained within this resource.
Each field contains one data item and is stored as an item (slice) in the Observation.component element.
BiRads Assessment Category component
Change In Definition component
Change In Number component
Change In Prominance component
Change In Size component
Change In State component
Density component
Margin component
MG AbnormalityFibroAdenoma Type component
Observed Count component
Orientation component
Shape component
Size component
Member Observations
The following are parts of this observation that are stored in seperate observation resources.
The reference to each external observation is stored as an item in the Observation.hasMember element.
'AIM Annotated Imaging Study' reference
'ImagingStudy' reference
Profile Fragments
The following are the fragments that are included in this profile. This is included for developers use to understand the hierarchy and commonality of disparate profiles..
BreastRad Observation NoDevice Fragment
BreastRad Observation NoValue Fragment
Imaging Study Fragment
MG Common Targets Fragment
MG Shape Targets Fragment
